The one-way analysis of variance (ANOVA) has been used to determine whether there are any statistically significant differences between the means of three or more independent groups. In particular, it evaluates the null hypothesis. Our null hypothesis (H

                           0
                        ) states that there are no significant differences in the SDGs practices among the countries, while the alternative hypothesis (H

                           1
                        ) states significant differences in the SDGs practices among the countries.
